natural solution: We can see that $\angle ACB = 40^\circ$ must be half of the central angle formed by the arc ${AB},$ or $80^\circ.$ Likewise, $\angle CAD = 30^\circ$ must be half of the central angle formed by the arc ${CD},$ or $60^\circ.$ Then, we can see that the angles formed by arcs ${BC}$ and ${DA}$ must sum to $360^\circ - (80^\circ + 60^\circ) = 220^\circ.$ That means the sum $\angle CAB + \angle ACD$ must be half of that, or $\boxed{110^\circ}.$
